    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add full Gemma4 multimodal model support (text + vision + audio) to TensorRT-LLM's PyTorch backend\n- Covers all 4 Gemma4 model variants: 26B-A4B-it (MoE, K=V), E2B-it (KV sharing, PLE), 31B-it, E4B-it\n- Implements all Gemma4-specific features: hybrid attention (per-layer head_dim 256/512), MoE (128 experts), K=V attention, KV sharing (via cache_layer_idx), Per-Layer Embeddings (PLE), double-wide MLP, logit softcapping, bidirectional mask, v_norm\n- Adds Gemma4 tool call parser for custom non-JSON format\n- Adds multimodal support: vision tower, audio tower, embedder, input processor\n- **Adds Triton prefill attention fallback** for head_dim=512 layers with bidirectional (custom) masks — solves trtllm-gen's lack of Custom mask cubin for H512\n- **CUDA graph support**: Fixed VSWA hybrid attention for CUDA graph capture/replay — unified trtllm-gen backend, fixed pool buffer sizing, `_block_tables` update in prepare()\n- **NVFP4 support**: Q is cast to FP8 alongside KV in the FlashInfer backend so trtllm-gen context cubins (`QkvE4m3OBfloat16`) work; uniform trtllm-gen backend across all layers; CUDA graphs work for both BF16 and NVFP4 paths\n- **V2 sliding-window eviction enabled**: `_util.py` uses the model's actual `sliding_window` for sliding layers' `max_attention_window`. V2 evicts old blocks beyond the window, dropping per-sequence sliding-pool block count from `ceil(max_seq_len/page_size)` to `ceil(sliding_window/page_size)` (≈4× sliding-pool memory reduction at typical configs). Unlocks much larger batch sizes on a single B200.\n- **Real model E2E validated**: all 4 BF16 models + the NVFP4 quantized 31B produce correct text output; 26B/31B multimodal with Triton prefill produces image descriptions consistent with HF reference\n\n### New Files\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `_torch/models/modeling_gemma4.py` | Text model: Attention, MoE, PLE, DecoderLayer, ForCausalLM |\n| `_torch/models/modeling_gemma4mm.py` | Multimodal: vision/audio towers, embedder, input processor, VLM wrapper |\n| `_torch/models/checkpoints/hf/gemma4_weight_mapper.py` | Weight loading with norm +1, K=V duplication, MoE remapping |\n| `_torch/attention_backend/triton_prefill.py` | Triton prefill kernel for head_dim=512 + custom mask (ported from sglang) |\n| `serve/tool_parser/gemma4_parser.py` | Tool call parser for Gemma4's custom format |\n| `tests/unittest/_torch/modeling/test_modeling_gemma4.py` | Text model tests: HF comparison + VSWA + CUDA graph + model defaults |\n| `tests/unittest/_torch/modeling/test_gemma4_e2e_dummy.py` | E2E tests with dummy configs/weights |\n| `tests/unittest/_torch/multimodal/test_gemma4_multimodal.py` | Multimodal tests (embedder, vision, input processor) |\n| `tests/unittest/_torch/attention_backend/test_triton_prefill.py` | Triton kernel tests (no-prefix + paged-prefix, custom + causal masks) |\n| `tests/unittest/_torch/executor/test_per_layer_head_dim.py` | Per-layer head_dim KV cache tests |\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n- **Hybrid attention**: Per-layer head_dim (256 sliding / 512 full) with unified trtllm-gen backend for all layers — avoids `flashinfer_backend` state leak between layers during CUDA graph capture\n- **Triton prefill fallback**: Embedded inside FlashInfer backend. Triggered only when `self.flashinfer_backend == \"trtllm-gen\"` + custom mask + context phase + k is not None. Two-stage kernel: stage 1 reads prefix KV from HND paged cache, stage 2 reads extend KV from contiguous tensors. Ported from sglang `extend_attention` with HND layout adaptation. Supports `custom_mask=None` with auto-generated causal mask.\n- **NVFP4 backend**: When the KV cache uses FP8 (NVFP4 checkpoints), the attention backend casts Q to FP8 alongside KV before plan/run, and passes `o_data_type=bfloat16` so the plan selects `QkvE4m3OBfloat16` cubins for both context and decode. This keeps a uniform trtllm-gen backend across all layers (CUDA graph compatible).\n- **KV sharing**: Handled via `cache_layer_idx` in Gemma4Attention — shared layers override the attention backend's `layer_idx` to read from target layer's KV cache slot\n- **VSWA page indices**: FlashInfer metadata detects VSWA (V2 per-pool), fetches per-pool page indices during prepare(), swaps correct pool before each layer's append/plan/run\n- **CUDA graph + VSWA**: `flashinfer_backend` passed as parameter to `plan()` (not stored on metadata); VSWA swap uses fixed-length copy for graph compatibility; trtllm-gen `_block_tables`/`_kv_lens_buffer` refreshed in `prepare()` before each graph replay\n- **V2 sliding-window eviction**: `_util.py` configures sliding layers' `max_attention_window` with the model's actual `sliding_window`. V2 evicts old blocks; FlashInfer's `prepare()` reads the currently-allocated block IDs per pool from V2, so the smaller post-eviction block count is picked up automatically.\n\n## Known Limitations\n\n1. **FlashInfer version**: Requires FlashInfer 0.6.7 + flashinfer-cubin from local `dmoss/trtllm-fmha-head-dim-512` branch for H512 trtllm-gen cubins on B200\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] Text model unit tests with HF numerical comparison, VSWA, CUDA graph (all pass)\n- [x] Multimodal component tests (all pass)\n- [x] Triton prefill kernel tests (all pass)\n- [x] Dummy-config E2E tests (all pass)\n- [x] Real model text-only E2E: all 4 BF16 models + NVFP4 quantized 31B (all pass)\n- [x] Multimodal E2E with Triton prefill: 26B + 31B (all pass)\n- [x] GSM8K + MMLU + MMMU + MMMU Pro + CoVoST 2 accuracy runs with CUDA graphs ON (all 5 models)\n- [x] V2 sliding-window eviction enabled and validated end-to-end on real models\n- [x] KV cache estimation: +3 tests for the V2 clamp-to-int invariant (replay of the fix, torch.randint float crash demo, int propagation through `_util.py`)\n- [x] MMMU Pro parser: 11 new tests covering `_ANSWER_RE` reverse-scan and `MMMU_PRO_PROMPT_MODE` env switch\n- [x] CoVoST normalizer: 8 new tests covering `_extract_translation` (AST response, case-insensitive marker, multi-marker picks last, marker-absent fallback, double-newline stop, empty input, post-marker normalization) + 1 prompt-format sanity check\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added support for Gemma4 models including multimodal vision capabilities\n  * Introduced CoVoST2, AIME 2025/2026, and MMMU Pro evaluation benchmarks\n  * Added Variable Sliding Window Attention (VSWA) support for optimized inference\n  * Enhanced Gemma4 tool-call parsing for improved function calling\n\n* **Improvements**\n  * Improved compatibility with transformers >= 5.0\n  * Updated attention backend selection and planning mechanisms\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
